  { title: 'Costa Rica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/costa-rica' },
  { title: 'Panama for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/panama' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'guatemalaFit', header: 'Guatemala Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$330-470/mo', guatemalaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$385-550/mo', guatemalaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$300-430/mo', guatemalaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'To 80', monthlyFrom: '$270-390/mo', guatemalaFit: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'Guatemalan Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: '$80-200/mo', guatemalaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$300-470', annual: '$3,600-5,640' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$410-620', annual: '$4,920-7,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$560-840', annual: '$6,720-10,080' },
  { category: 'Guatemala Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: '$30-80/visit' },
  { category: 'Guatemala Public', monthly: 'Free/nominal', annual: 'Limited quality' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Guatemala 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Guatemala. Lake Atitlan beauty, Mayan culture, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Guatemala"
  subheadline="Guatemala offers Lake Atitlan stunning beauty, rich Mayan culture, extremely affordable living, and established expat communities—Central America hidden gem for budget retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/guatemala-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Guatemala</h2>
  <p>
    Guatemala offers extraordinary value—Lake Atitlan is one of the world most beautiful lakes, Mayan culture is living tradition, costs are extremely low, and expat communities are well-established. Antigua colonial charm and eternal spring climate attract many retirees.
  </p>

  <p>
    Lake Atitlan area offers stunning volcanic scenery with expat villages. Antigua provides colonial architecture near Guatemala City healthcare. Guatemala City has best medical facilities. Each region offers distinct character and cost advantages.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Guatemala City best</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish; Mayan languages in highlands</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $1,000-2,000/month; very low</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Eternal spring in highlands</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Mayan culture; colonial heritage; natural beauty</li>
      <li><strong>Value:</strong> Among Central America most affordable</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Guatemala Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Guatemala healthcare is concentrated in Guatemala City—Hospital Herrera Llerandi, Centro Medico are decent private options. Outside the capital, quality drops significantly. Lake Atitlan area has very limited healthcare; serious cases require Guatemala City (3+ hours) or evacuation.
  </p>

  <p>
    International insurance with evacuation coverage is essential for seniors outside Guatemala City. Many expats use Guatemala City private hospitals for serious needs while paying cash for local routine care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Healthcare Centralized in Capital</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Quality healthcare is concentrated in Guatemala City. Lake Atitlan and Antigua have limited facilities—serious conditions require capital travel. Consider Guatemala City accessibility when choosing retirement location. Evacuation to US (Houston, Miami) is option for complex cases.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Guatemala has flexible options:
  </p>

  <h3>Pensionado Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with $1,000+/month guaranteed pension income. Straightforward process; permanent residence. Tax benefits and import duty exemptions available.
  </p>

  <h3>Rentista Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with investment income—demonstrate $1,000+/month from investments. Similar benefits to pensionado.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    90-day visa-free for many nationalities. Extensions possible. Some retirees use extended stays while pursuing formal residence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Guatemala:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pensionado visa:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Essential given limited local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Critical for Lake Atitlan/highland residents</li>
    <li><strong>US access:</strong> Houston/Miami evacuation option valuable</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Guatemala</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for Guatemala seniors—local healthcare is limited. Plan must include evacuation to Guatemala City and US. Routine care can be cash payment locally; international coverage for serious needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Guatemala, international coverage with Americas evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Guatemala</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Americas network, US evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Blue Cross network for US evacuation (Houston, Miami)</li>
    <li><strong>IMG Global:</strong> Budget-friendly with evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with evacuation essential for Guatemala.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Guatemala are moderate given need for international coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Guatemalan private care is affordable for routine</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Consultations $30-50; affordable cash payment</li>
    <li><strong>Americas-only:</strong> Skip worldwide coverage if not traveling globally</li>
    <li><strong>Guatemala City access:</strong> Keep within reach for healthcare</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Budget Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,400/month Social Security. Seeking maximum value.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pensionado visa. Cigna Global with US evacuation. Lake Atitlan living.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~$380/month. Stunning beauty; excellent value on Social Security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Canadian Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension CAD 2,800/month. Antigua colonial charm.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Guatemala City 45 minutes for healthcare.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~$900/month combined. Colonial living; capital healthcare accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Spanish Teacher, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,200/month pension. Teaching Spanish part-time. Quetzaltenango.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> IMG Global budget coverage. Local cash payment for routine.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> IMG ~$300/month. Highland living; teaching income supplements.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Guatemala safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mixed—tourist areas and expat communities are generally safe. Guatemala City has high crime in some areas. Lake Atitlan and Antigua are relatively safe. Standard precautions apply. Many expats live comfortably with awareness of surroundings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Lake Atitlan really that beautiful?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—consistently rated one of world most beautiful lakes. Volcanic setting, Mayan villages, stunning scenery. Aldous Huxley called it "too much of a good thing." Expat communities in Panajachel and San Marcos are well-established.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Guatemala?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very affordable—among Central America lowest costs. Comfortable retirement possible on $1,000-1,500/month. Domestic help affordable. Dining out $5-15. Rent $300-800 for decent accommodation. Extreme value for those seeking budget retirement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Spanish?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Essential—English is limited outside some tourist areas and expat enclaves. Spanish language schools are excellent and affordable in Antigua and Quetzaltenango. Learning Spanish significantly improves daily life.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes with evacuation coverage essential for Guatemala.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Guatemalan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
